{
  "doc_id": "25620",
  "text": "Coinfection with schistosomiasis and HIV does occur in areas where both infections are endemic. There are only a few epidemiologic studies on S. mansoni coinfection with HIV, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and only one on coinfection with S. haematobium. [CITATION_5] Consequently, a lot remains unknown about the interactions between S. haematobium and HIV with respect to treatment efficacy, pattern of acquired immunity, clinical manifestations, and diagnosis.",
